        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-08T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-08T23:00:00-05:00" n="1669" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1669">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.313/8–949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-09T12:00:00+08:00">August 9, 1949—noon.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 16—3:33 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 903. Concur suggestion Chungking that American citizens should be informed
                    Consulate closing at time Communists enter Szechuan province, Chungking’s 140,
                    August 5 to Department, repeated Canton 94.</p>
                <p>As matter shaping up here, it is entirely possible Government will not move
                    Chungking but that should it do so it will be mere facade with plane standing by
                    to airlift it Taiwan slightest provocation. With Communist armies entering
                    Szediuan, Nationalist Government would likely take announcement withdrawal more
                    as blow at Communists than as lack confidence Nationalist Government.</p>
                <p>Sent Department Cantel 903, Chungking 78.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
